title: $A softer amid 9pct spike in oil prices
text:
Tue, Sep 1, 2015, 7:13 AM AEST - Australia Markets open in 2 hrs 47 mins $A softer amid 9pct spike in oil prices AAP – 23 minutes ago Print 
The Australian dollar has crept lower despite a weaker greenback and a spike in most commodities. 
At 0630 AEST on Tuesday, the currency was trading at 71.17 US cents, down from 71.42 cents on Monday. 
Overnight, nervous investors sold down global equities and the US dollar while US crude oil closed nearly nine per cent higher as the US government lowered its domestic production estimate. 
CURRENCY SNAPSHOT AT 0630 AEST ON TUESDAY 
One Australian dollar buys: 
* 71.17 US cents, from 71.42 cents on Monday 
* 86.29 Japanese yen, from 86.54 yen 
* 63.48 euro cents, from 63.62 euro cents 
(*Currency closes taken at 1700 AEST previous local session) 
Source: IRESS Data unlikely to be helpful for Hockey AAP
